				<!-- google_ad_section_start --><p>I have to agree with you here. I have a daughter that is turning 14 in Nov. She is a cheerleader, goes to a performing arts school, yada yada yada. Now, is great because she is outgoing. BUT..she is not so outgoing with her family at home. Thinking back though, I think most teenagers are like this at some point. The thing is, it is almost a &#8220;cool&#8221; thing to do to act as if your home life is hard, you are not understood, etc. In this way, somehow the teenager&#8217;s identify with each other and it is &#8220;their team&#8221; type of attitude. Regardless of the fact they are irritating as all h&#235;ll sometimes, there intentions are probably innocent. BUT&#8230;watch out for those boys!! That is my peeve at the moment with my daughter. She thinks she is so grown up in High School, etc. Uggh! Hey this is your blog, not mine right!??  Keith</p>
